I forked a GitHub repo roguecommunitycollegewebdevelopers/roguebookexchange.git to bagjsr/roguebookexchange.git and want to keep it updated.
Track
+

After I forked the repo to your Github account, I did this one time:
+

git clone git@github.com:roguecommunitycollegewebdevelopers/roguebookexchange.git
cd roguebookexchange
git remote add upstream git@github.com:roguecommunitycollegewebdevelopers/roguebookexchange.git

Update
+

Each time I want to update, from my local master branch:
+

git fetch upstream
git rebase upstream/master
